      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Your symptoms are classic signs of dry eye syndrome, which is a common and treatable condition. You can absolutely start using over-the-counter lubricating eye drops immediately to relieve the redness and stickiness. Just ensure you choose a preservative-free formula if you plan to use them frequently, and try to follow the 20-20-20 rule to reduce screen strain. If the redness persists or pain worsens, you should see an optometrist, but for now, your drops are the right first step.",
