      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The thick, yellowish discharge and eyelid swelling are classic signs of a bacterial infection, likely a stye or conjunctivitis, which is why you should absolutely visit a clinic or optometrist immediately. Do not delay; these conditions can spread to your other eye or cause permanent damage if left untreated. While warm compresses might help soothe the discomfort, they cannot cure an infection, and relying solely on drops is dangerous here. Please get your eyes checked today to prevent a serious complication.",
      "source": "target",
